Stan Branco is a professional rodeo athlete known for his skills in steer wrestling, tie-down roping, and team roping. He is a fifth-generation rodeo athlete, continuing the legacy of the Branco family in the rodeo arena. Born and raised in Chowchilla, California, Branco has been competing professionally since 2006.

Here you can follow Stan Branco’s net worth, career earnings, career, biography, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Stan Branco

Born into a family steeped in rodeo tradition, Stan Branco hails from Chowchilla, California. He is a third-generation cowboy on his father’s side and a fifth-generation cowboy on his mother’s side.

His family’s rodeo legacy includes his grandfather, Dan Branco, who qualified for the National Finals Rodeo (NFR) nine times as a team roper.

Professional Career

Branco’s career highlights include qualifying for the National Finals Rodeo (NFR) twice, first in 2013 and then a decade later in 2023.

He has also won several major rodeos, including the 2022 California Circuit Steer Wrestling & All-Around Champion, the Lakeside, CA Rodeo, and the King City, CA Stampede.

In 2023, he tied the arena record at Rodeo Austin, securing the championship and nearly doubling his Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) earnings.

Stan Branco’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Stan Branco’s net worth is estimated to be $3 million.

His career earnings as of November 2023 stood at $571,760.

Career Earnings

Stan Branco, a professional rodeo athlete, has had a successful career with significant earnings. As of November 2023, his career earnings total $571,760.

In 2022 alone, he earned $59,150. Some of his notable earnings from individual events include more than $9,500 from a season, $9,457 from the Caldwell Night Rodeo, and $2,271 from the 2023 San Angelo Rodeo.

These earnings have contributed to his overall career earnings and reflect his success in the rodeo arena.

Personal Details

Wife

Stan is married to Professional Breakaway Roper, Kate Branco, and they welcomed their first child, a boy named Riggs, in July 2022.

How old is Stan Branco?

As of 2023, he is 37.

How tall is he?

Stan stands at 6 ft 4 inches tall.

What is his nationality?

He is American.

Career Highlights

  • Career earnings: $571,760
  • NFR Qualifications: 1 (2013)
  • 2022 world standings place: 13th (AA), 28th (SW), 227th (TD)
  • 2022 earnings: $59,150 (AA), $51,220 (SW), $5,384

2023 Highlights

Steer Wrestling

• Won Rodeo Austin (Texas) 

• Won the Sandhills Stock Show & Rodeo (Odessa, Texas)

• Won the Lakeside (Calif.) Rodeo

• Won the Santa Maria (Calif.) Elks Rodeo

• Won the Caldwell (Idaho) Night Rodeo

• Won the Sheriff’s PRCA Rodeo (San Bernardino, Calif.)

• Won the Kern County Fair & Rodeo (Bakersfield, Calif.)

• Co-champion at the Eugene (Ore.) Pro Rodeo

• Co-champion at the Ramona (Calif.) Rodeo

FAQs About Stan Branco 

What is Stan Branco’s Net Worth?

$3 million.

Who is his wife?

Kate Branco, professional breakaway roper.

When did he join PRCA?

2006.
